WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.420
I spoke about an old acquaintance with BV first. This is a first-in-human trial of

00:00:05.420 --> 00:00:13.860
BI-1808, a tumor necrosis factor 2 or TNFR2 blocker depleter in T-cell lymphomas.

00:00:15.360 --> 00:00:23.900
So BI-1808 is an IgG1 monoclonal antibody that targets TNF2 and thereby inhibits the interaction

00:00:23.900 --> 00:00:32.380
between the TNF2 receptor and the ligand, which is TNF-alpha. TNFR2 is overexpressed in many T-cell

00:00:32.380 --> 00:00:38.580
lymphomas, but also on immune cells in the tumor microenvironment. And when it is overexpressed,

00:00:38.580 --> 00:00:44.880
it can promote cancer progression. And early clinical data has shown that there is single

00:00:44.880 --> 00:00:52.280
agent activity in several various solid cancers. In addition to direct killing through ADCC of the

00:00:52.280 --> 00:00:53.860
malignant T-cells,

00:00:53.900 --> 00:01:00.600
we also see a depletion of Tregs and an expansion of effector T-cells and reprogramming of the tumor

00:01:00.600 --> 00:01:08.280
microenvironment, including myeloid cells. So here is just a graphic depiction of what

00:01:08.280 --> 00:01:18.920
BI-1808 does. So without BI-1808, you have CD4-positive cells that have high expression

00:01:18.920 --> 00:01:23.680
of TNFR2, and they can help and promote tumor cell growth.

00:01:23.900 --> 00:01:31.400
And they can help and prevent the influx of CD8-positive effector cells. Now, if you add BI-1808,

00:01:31.400 --> 00:01:41.820
you deplete these CD4-TNF2 receptor high cells, T-regulatory cells, and you allow activated CD8 T-cells

00:01:41.820 --> 00:01:50.900
that are low in TNF receptor 2 to exert immune killing of the tumor cells.

00:01:50.900 --> 00:02:01.400
So BI-1808 is a phase one, phase two study. Initially started with all advanced malignancies,

00:02:01.400 --> 00:02:06.520
and the dose escalation proportion of that has been completed.

00:02:06.520 --> 00:02:13.180
It then moved to the phase 2a with a signal-seeking dose in T-cell lymphoma, and particularly CTCL,

00:02:13.180 --> 00:02:18.900
and that's what I will be talking about. And currently, a dose optimization cohort is going on,

00:02:18.900 --> 00:02:26.840
so BI-1808 is given every three weeks, IV, and we will be exploring a low dose of 250 milligram

00:02:26.840 --> 00:02:31.520
every three weeks as compared to the high dose of 1,000 milligram every three weeks.

00:02:31.520 --> 00:02:38.660
For the CTCL cohort, the key eligibility criteria are very standard, 18 years plus, good performance

00:02:38.660 --> 00:02:46.020
status. Stage 1b plus is allowed, so including MF and cesarean patients, at least one prior therapy,

00:02:46.020 --> 00:02:48.900
and not eligible for standard of care.

00:02:48.900 --> 00:02:56.400
Adequate organ function, measurable disease, no CNS involvement, no large cell transformation is allowed.

00:02:56.400 --> 00:03:08.020
So this is the early efficacy data of 21 patients were enrolled, but only 13 patients with CTCL were response

00:03:08.020 --> 00:03:16.000
available, and two patients with PTCL. For the CTCL patients, here depicted is the M-SWAT, which is the way of how

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:18.720
we assess skin disease.

00:03:18.720 --> 00:03:29.300
So the modified severity-weighted assessment tools, and you can see that there is an overall response rate of 46% with one

00:03:29.300 --> 00:03:37.340
patient with Cesarean syndrome who achieved a complete response, and all, except for one patient with Cesarean syndrome

00:03:37.340 --> 00:03:43.040
having at least stable disease, which is something important in this otherwise difficult-to-treat population.

00:03:43.040 --> 00:03:48.540
Of the two PTCL patients, one had APR and the other one had stable disease.

00:03:48.720 --> 00:03:57.220
Here is the SWMR plot, just showing that essentially responses can be very durable, and patients even with stable disease,

00:03:57.220 --> 00:04:05.300
which can be meaningful in this disease, as I mentioned, can stay on the drug for quite some time.

00:04:05.300 --> 00:04:10.100
Looking at the correlatives, it does as it was promised on the graph.

00:04:10.100 --> 00:04:17.980
So we have biopsies before and after, and we see a significant increase in CD8 infiltration and accompanying

00:04:17.980 --> 00:04:23.280
grandson B elevation at just five weeks after start of therapy.

00:04:23.280 --> 00:04:27.320
In terms of side effects, it's a very safe agent.

00:04:27.320 --> 00:04:39.920
And while we've seen, of course, 81% of any treatment emergent adverse effect, only one patient really had a grade 3 adverse event or serious

00:04:39.920 --> 00:04:49.020
adverse event secondary to BI-1808, and that is most consistent with a disease flare, so a skin reaction followed by pyrexia.

00:04:49.020 --> 00:05:02.480
Disease flares are fairly common and are characterized by increased itching, skin peeling, erythema, and happen early on in several of the patients.

00:05:02.480 --> 00:05:09.740
And we think it is because of that influx of the CD8 positive T cells.

00:05:09.740 --> 00:05:20.320
In summary, the signal-seeking cohort of single-agent BI-1808 for T cell lymphoma shows promising efficacy and is associated with a strong immune activation.

00:05:20.320 --> 00:05:31.560
We see an objective response rate of 46% in patients with advanced cutaneous T cell lymphoma, and the study is currently moving on to the dose optimization cohort.

00:05:31.560 --> 00:05:37.360
BI-1808 was well tolerated and allowed the exploration of combinations with other agents.

00:05:37.360 --> 00:05:39.560
There is another cohort going on.

00:05:39.560 --> 00:05:52.520
We see a significant increase in the number of patients with T cell lymphoma with T cell lymphoma with T cell lymphoma with T cell lymphoma of BI-1808 combined with pembrolizumab in CTCL, and also of BI-1808 with various chemotherapeutic agents in solid tumors, particularly in ovarian cancer.

00:05:52.520 --> 00:05:56.680
And giving you back a minute for the next few speakers.

00:05:56.840 --> 00:05:57.200
Thank you.
